{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6ae06f3-e1fe-4d6d-b489-d4862c33448c","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs. Here's the breakdown for your project:\n\n| Target Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? | Action Needed |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes | None |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No | Upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No | Upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for modern .NET targets (while .NET Framework 4.6.2+ remains supported). Both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are end-of-life and were dropped.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nThen upgrade the MSTest packages to v3. Want me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"50236330-2fbd-4c99-9e38-2c0cc80bd106","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They're using MSTest v2 (2.2.10) and want to migrate to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs. Let me recall:\n\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum:\n  - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/modern .NET)\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (this should be fine since they have net462)\n  - netcoreapp3.1 was dropped in MSTest v3\n  \nSo the compatibility issue is clear: both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are no longer supported in MSTest v3 since they're out of support themselves. They'll need to upgrade those target frameworks to at least `net6.0`, while `net462` should remain compatible.","outputTokens":549,"requestId":"042A:34D8DE:163AAE2:17AE52D:6A033806"},"id":"fcaeb086-df4a-4d06-9174-2e464660acbe","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:22.002Z","parentId":"293580d3-0c1f-4d07-a6fd-75d314ca7138"}
